cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the automation of high-value derivatives contracts, which involves aspects of cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and distributed computing (cs.DC). While the paper does not delve deeply into any one of these sub-categories, it touches on each of them in some way, making them all likely candidates for classification.
